quoteFirst: Then we continued our wearisome tramp. An age seemed to pass. I looked at my watch, but it was only
quoteLast: . To and fro we went with bruised shoulders, aching backs and numbed intelligence. I fell into a kind of semi-conscious state. Suddenly the whistle blew for lunch.
title: Combed Out
author: Voigt, F. A. (Frederick Augustus), 1892-1957

quoteLast: ; and on the 29th sets at 11:28 p. m. It is farthest from the earth on the 13th at 1:30 p. m.; and nearest to the earth on the 26th at 3:42 a. m.

quoteFirst: “The signalman, acting as second in command,” said Morgan, swelling, “then informed destroyer flotilla that _Cryptic_ and _Devolution_ had made good defects, and, in obedience to Admiral’s supplementary orders (I was afraid they might suspect that, but they didn’t), had proceeded at seven knots at
quoteLast: to rendezvous near Channel Islands, seven miles N.N.W. the Casquet light. (I’ve rendezvoused there myself, Sir.) Destroyer flotilla would therefore follow cruisers and catch up with them on their course.
title: Traffics and Discoveries
